CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 3, 1963, pg. 17, reads: "Max Roach and Crew in Action - Left to right, bassist Eddie Kahn, pianist Ron Matthews (back turned), tenor Saxman Clifford Jordan and drummer Max Roach are working out on Thelonius Monk's 'Well You Needn't,' before appreciative Grill fans. Roach broke all Grill records during his stay at the Wylie Ave. emporium."
TitMainTitle: Max Roach's band including Eddie Kahn on bass, Ron Mathews on piano, Clifford Jordan on tenor saxophone, and Max Roach on drums, on stage in Crawford Grill No. 2, another version
